    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "content": "Loops <i></i> are a way to iterate multiple times through a set of questions or tasks. Loops can “embed” any of the step types exiting in the system, marking it highly powerful."
    },
    {
      "type": "h2",
      "content": "1.2.5.2. Creating Loops in the Editor"
    },
    {
      "type": "numbers",
      "points": [
        {
          "text":"Select the Loop Step icon: <i></i>"
        },
        {
          "text":"Choose where you want to put the Loop Step in the orange bar below"
        },
        {
          "text":"Add Loop text to the input field"
        },
        {
          "text":"Set the amount of iterations"
        },
        {
          "text":"Add different <a href='#/section/template-anatomy/input-elements'>Input elements</a> into the Loop Step to loop over"
        },
        {
          "text":"Validate the Step by clicking the green tick: <i></i>"
        }
      ]
    },
